    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing procedure code handling in S1AP successful outcome encoder\n\n### Summary\nThe S1AP eNB encoder was missing support for several procedure codes in the successful outcome encoding path, causing encoding failures when handling S1Setup, PathSwitchRequest, and E_RABModificationIndication procedures. This inconsistency between the encoder and decoder led to unexpected behavior during S1AP message processing.\n\nThe issue was identified when testing handover scenarios where PathSwitchRequest successful outcomes failed to encode properly, resulting in dropped UE context modifications.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/S1AP/s1ap_eNB_encoder.c`: Added missing procedure code cases in `s1ap_eNB_encode_successfull_outcome` function for S1Setup, PathSwitchRequest, and E_RABModificationIndication\n- `openair3/S1AP/s1ap_eNB_encoder.c`: Fixed spelling inconsistencies in log messages (\"successfull\" \u2192 \"successful\", \"unsuccessfull\" \u2192 \"unsuccessful\")\n- `openair3/S1AP/s1ap_eNB_encoder.c`: Updated unsuccessful outcome encoder to match decoder supported procedure codes\n\n"
}